cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper discusses gait recognition, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel method for learning discriminative human body parts, which involves machine learning techniques, making it likely to belong to the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the non-invasive and behavioral nature of gait recognition, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper uses a benchmark database for experiments, which relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and the use of machine learning techniques for recognition suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence sub-category (cs.AI).
